{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UofLpct1XgzBTCtrT8zT6U","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Test Setup Pattern Analysis\n\nHere's the full breakdown of the test setup pattern in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/auth-routes.test.ts`:\n\n### **1. App Creation**\n- Uses **Hono** framework (lightweight HTTP framework)\n- App is created fresh in each test via `beforeEach`:\n  ```typescript\n  app = new Hono();\n  app.route(\"/auth\", createAuthRoutes({ ... }));\n  ```\n- Routes are mounted at `/auth` prefix\n- Requests are made via `app.request()` method (no actual server startup)\n\n### **2. Database Setup**\n\n**Raw SQL Connection:**\n- Uses `postgres` package with `DATABASE_URL` from env (defaults to `postgresql://vscode@localhost:5432/rng_utopia_dev`)\n- Established once in `beforeAll`, torn down in `afterAll` with `await rawSql.end()`\n\n**Tables Created:**\n- `auth_challenges` — stores nonce, wallet, message, expiration, usage flag\n- `refresh_tokens` — stores token hash, family_id, expiration, revocation flag\n\n**Data Cleanup:**\n- Each test runs with fresh tables via `beforeEach`: `TRUNCATE auth_challenges, refresh_tokens RESTART IDENTITY`\n\n**AuthDb Abstraction:**\n- Wraps raw SQL with `createAuthDb(rawSql)` \n- Passed to route handlers as `authDb` parameter\n\n### **3. Auth/JWT Setup**\n\n**JWT Secret:**\n- Test-specific secret: `new TextEncoder().encode(\"test-secret-for-auth-route-tests\")`\n- Passed to route handler config\n- Verified with `jwtVerify()` from `jose` library using `HS256` algorithm\n\n**JWT Content:**\n- Access token contains `sub` claim (subject) = wallet address\n- Verified in tests via: `const { payload } = await jwtVerify(tokens.accessToken, JWT_SECRET, { algorithms: [\"HS256\"] })`\n\n**Token TTLs Configured:**\n- `accessTokenTtlSeconds: 3600`\n- `refreshTokenTtlDays: 14`\n- `challengeTtlSeconds: 300`\n\n### **4. Mocks Used**\n\n**Stub Database (Db):**\n- Minimal mock for non-auth DB operations:\n  ```typescript\n  const stubDb = {\n    getProfileByWallet: async () => null,\n    createPlayerProfile: async () => ({} as any),\n  } as unknown as Db;\n  ```\n- Only two methods stubbed; returns null/empty objects\n\n**Real Keypair for Crypto:**\n- `Keypair.generate()` from `@solana/web3.js` creates real Ed25519 keypairs\n- Signatures created with NaCl (`nacl.sign.detached()`)\n- Signatures encoded as base58 strings (`bs58.encode()`)\n\n### **5. Test Flow Pattern**\n\nThe main integration test demonstrates the complete flow:\n\n1. **Challenge** — POST `/auth/challenge` with wallet → returns nonce + message\n2. **Sign** — Client signs message with `nacl.sign.detached()`\n3. **Verify** — POST `/auth/verify` with nonce + wallet + signature → returns access + refresh tokens\n4. **Refresh** — POST `/auth/refresh` with old refresh token → returns new tokens, old token rotated out\n5. **Logout** — POST `/auth/logout` with refresh token → revokes token (204 response)\n6. **Validation** — Retired tokens fail on reuse (401 with \"reuse\" error)\n\n### **6. Key Security Tests Included**\n\n- Wrong wallet claim with valid signature → 401\n- Signature from wrong keypair → 401\n- Nonce reuse prevention → 401 on second use\n- Invalid refresh token → 401\n- Token rotation on refresh (new token differs from old)\n\nAll requests use standard HTTP with JSON bodies; no bearer token headers for these specific endpoints (tokens are passed in body)."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f9901d53-ab05-422c-a65b-76ea18fa6c39","uuid":"17e74442-f647-4289-809a-110a554da41e","timestamp":"2026-03-31T15:32:54.577Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the file /workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/auth-routes.test.ts and report back the full contents. I need to understand the test setup pattern (how app is created, how DB is set up, how auth/JWT works in tests, what mocks are used).","agentId":"a349e5b1e566d9a9f","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Test Setup Pattern Analysis\n\nHere's the full breakdown of the test setup pattern in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/auth-routes.test.ts`:\n\n### **1. App Creation**\n- Uses **Hono** framework (lightweight HTTP framework)\n- App is created fresh in each test via `beforeEach`:\n  ```typescript\n  app = new Hono();\n  app.route(\"/auth\", createAuthRoutes({ ... }));\n  ```\n- Routes are mounted at `/auth` prefix\n- Requests are made via `app.request()` method (no actual server startup)\n\n### **2. Database Setup**\n\n**Raw SQL Connection:**\n- Uses `postgres` package with `DATABASE_URL` from env (defaults to `postgresql://vscode@localhost:5432/rng_utopia_dev`)\n- Established once in `beforeAll`, torn down in `afterAll` with `await rawSql.end()`\n\n**Tables Created:**\n- `auth_challenges` — stores nonce, wallet, message, expiration, usage flag\n- `refresh_tokens` — stores token hash, family_id, expiration, revocation flag\n\n**Data Cleanup:**\n- Each test runs with fresh tables via `beforeEach`: `TRUNCATE auth_challenges, refresh_tokens RESTART IDENTITY`\n\n**AuthDb Abstraction:**\n- Wraps raw SQL with `createAuthDb(rawSql)` \n- Passed to route handlers as `authDb` parameter\n\n### **3. Auth/JWT Setup**\n\n**JWT Secret:**\n- Test-specific secret: `new TextEncoder().encode(\"test-secret-for-auth-route-tests\")`\n- Passed to route handler config\n- Verified with `jwtVerify()` from `jose` library using `HS256` algorithm\n\n**JWT Content:**\n- Access token contains `sub` claim (subject) = wallet address\n- Verified in tests via: `const { payload } = await jwtVerify(tokens.accessToken, JWT_SECRET, { algorithms: [\"HS256\"] })`\n\n**Token TTLs Configured:**\n- `accessTokenTtlSeconds: 3600`\n- `refreshTokenTtlDays: 14`\n- `challengeTtlSeconds: 300`\n\n### **4. Mocks Used**\n\n**Stub Database (Db):**\n- Minimal mock for non-auth DB operations:\n  ```typescript\n  const stubDb = {\n    getProfileByWallet: async () => null,\n    createPlayerProfile: async () => ({} as any),\n  } as unknown as Db;\n  ```\n- Only two methods stubbed; returns null/empty objects\n\n**Real Keypair for Crypto:**\n- `Keypair.generate()` from `@solana/web3.js` creates real Ed25519 keypairs\n- Signatures created with NaCl (`nacl.sign.detached()`)\n- Signatures encoded as base58 strings (`bs58.encode()`)\n\n### **5. Test Flow Pattern**\n\nThe main integration test demonstrates the complete flow:\n\n1. **Challenge** — POST `/auth/challenge` with wallet → returns nonce + message\n2. **Sign** — Client signs message with `nacl.sign.detached()`\n3. **Verify** — POST `/auth/verify` with nonce + wallet + signature → returns access + refresh tokens\n4. **Refresh** — POST `/auth/refresh` with old refresh token → returns new tokens, old token rotated out\n5. **Logout** — POST `/auth/logout` with refresh token → revokes token (204 response)\n6. **Validation** — Retired tokens fail on reuse (401 with \"reuse\" error)\n\n### **6. Key Security Tests Included**\n\n- Wrong wallet claim with valid signature → 401\n- Signature from wrong keypair → 401\n- Nonce reuse prevention → 401 on second use\n- Invalid refresh token → 401\n- Token rotation on refresh (new token differs from old)\n\nAll requests use standard HTTP with JSON bodies; no bearer token headers for these specific endpoints (tokens are passed in body)."}],"totalDurationMs":12895,"totalTokens":32831,"totalToolUseCount":1,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6181,"cache_read_input_tokens":25681,"output_tokens":964,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6181},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
