{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XTJDDLrAJBf3ugVpnMmc5L","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nHere are the three route files with their full contents and key insights:\n\n### 1. **profile.ts** — Authenticated player routes\n\n**Purpose**: Manages profile data and transaction history for authenticated players.\n\n**Key Routes**:\n- `GET /me` — Fetches authenticated player's full profile including username, avatar, stats, win streaks, and game breakdown. Requires wallet from context.\n- `PUT /username` — Updates player username with validation and 30-day cooldown enforcement.\n- `GET /transactions` — Paginated transaction history with optional game filtering. Returns up to 50 transactions per page.\n- `POST /confirm-tx` — Records confirmed on-chain transactions (deposits, refunds) with game and match info.\n\n**Dependencies**: \n- Requires `Db` interface for database operations\n- Uses context middleware to extract `wallet` from JWT\n- Game name mapping (frontend ↔ DB names, e.g., \"lord-of-rngs\" ↔ \"lord\")\n\n**Auth Pattern**: All routes check for `wallet` in context (set by earlier middleware) and return 401 if missing.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **public-profile.ts** — Unauthenticated profile lookup\n\n**Purpose**: Exposes limited public player profiles without authentication.\n\n**Key Routes**:\n- `GET /:identifier` — Lookup public profile by user_id or username. Returns username, avatar, heat multiplier, and basic stats (games played, wins, win rate). No sensitive data like balance or wager amounts.\n\n**Dependencies**:\n- `Db` interface for lookups\n- No authentication required\n\n---\n\n### 3. **auth.ts** — JWT session management with challenge-response\n\n**Purpose**: Implements cryptographic wallet authentication and token management.\n\n**Key Routes**:\n- `POST /challenge` — Generates a random nonce and a human-readable message for the player to sign with their Solana wallet. Message includes wallet, cluster, nonce, issuance/expiry times.\n- `POST /verify` — Consumes the challenge (atomic), verifies Ed25519 signature using TweetNaCl, auto-creates player profile if needed, and issues JWT access token + opaque refresh token.\n- `POST /refresh` — Rotates refresh token. Detects token reuse (security feature) by checking if previous token was revoked. Issues new access token and refresh token in same family.\n- `POST /logout` — Revokes refresh token (returns 204 No Content regardless of success).\n\n**Dependencies**:\n- `AuthDb` — challenge and refresh token storage\n- `Db` — player profile creation\n- `jwtSecret` (Uint8Array) — HS256 key\n- Configuration: `cluster`, `challengeTtlSeconds`, `accessTokenTtlSeconds`, `refreshTokenTtlDays`\n\n**Auth Flow**:\n1. Client calls `/challenge` with wallet → gets nonce and message\n2. Client signs message with wallet's private key → calls `/verify` with nonce, wallet, signature\n3. Server verifies signature with `nacl.sign.detached.verify()` against public key (wallet address)\n4. On success: access token (short-lived JWT) + refresh token (opaque, long-lived, hashed in DB)\n5. Client uses access token as Bearer header for authenticated routes\n6. When access token expires, client uses refresh token at `/refresh` to get new pair\n\n**Security Features**:\n- Challenge consumption is atomic (prevents replay)\n- Wallet must match challenge (prevents cross-wallet replay)\n- Signature verification (Ed25519, Solana standard)\n- Refresh token reuse detection with family revocation (token compromise protection)\n- Refresh tokens are hashed in DB (not plaintext)"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f9901d53-ab05-422c-a65b-76ea18fa6c39","uuid":"5878e976-19e7-4019-846e-bf23a95281cf","timestamp":"2026-03-31T15:32:55.461Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read these files and report their full contents:\n1. /workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/routes/profile.ts\n2. /workspaces/rng-utopia/backen